===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|mer|id1=die|wedʰ}}
From {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|morgage}}, {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|mortgage}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|mort gage||death pledge}}, after a translation of judicial {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|mortuum vadium}} or {{m|la|mortuum wadium}}, from {{m|la|mortuum}} + {{m|la|vadium}} or {{m|la|wadium}}, of {{etyl|gem|en}} ({{etyl|frk|en}}) origin, from a root *''waddi'', ''wadja''. Compare {{m|en|gage}} and also {{m|en|wage}}. So called because the deal dies either when the debt is paid or when payment fails.

